##Dr. Li Wenliang, who was the first to warn of new pneumonia, is gone

Health insight

Functional introduction, understand the health professional news

There are no heroes who fall from the sky, only mortals who rise up.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Dr. Li Wen-liang has left.

At 3:48 a.m. on February 7,2020, Wuhan Central Hospital Weibo posted the news: Our ophthalmologist, Li Wenliang, had an unfortunate infection during the work of fighting the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic. All efforts to save him were futile, at 2:58 a.m. on February 7,2020, our deepest sympathies and condolences.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A few hours earlier, around 22 p.m. on Feb. 6, the news of Li's death had spread among many people's wechat groups and friends.

Li Wenliang was one of the first to warn of a new outbreak of pneumonia. On the evening of December 30,2019, he sent a message to a group of classmates. A few days later, on January 3,2020, he was reprimanded by the local police station for "making false statements on the Internet. ". And then go back to work.

On 8 January, he contracted the infection during his examination and began to cough on 10 January. After 16, he developed dyspnea and was unable to get out of bed at all. On 1 February, he was diagnosed as new crown pneumonia. On February 5th, his condition deteriorated.

It was revealed that Li Wenliang was taken to the emergency room at around 19 PM on February 6. At 21:18, the epinephrine was administered, the heart stopped at 21:30, the ECOM was administered, and the epinephrine was administered again at 23:58.

At 00:38 on February 7, Wuhan Central Hospital Weibo posted news: "in the fight against the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic, our hospital ophthalmologist Li Wenliang unfortunate infection, currently critically ill, is in full rescue. ".

At the bottom of the message, the first message was: NO MORE SLEEP! Wait for a Miracle Online!

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Before this Li Wenliang accepts the media interview, also through the writing to tell the reporter, "after the recovery I want to return to the front line work quickly, continues sees a doctor for the patient. "

Instead of a miracle, however, there was the sad news.

Warning: A healthy society should not have only one voice

Li Wenliang was one of the first to warn of a new outbreak of pneumonia.

Li Wenliang was born in 1986, born in Beizhen, Jinzhou City, Liaoning Province. In 2004, he enrolled in a seven-year program in clinical medicine at the Wuhan University. After graduating, he worked briefly in Xiamen for three years before returning to Wuhan to work at the Wuhan Central Hospital.

On December 30,2019, Li Wenliang saw a patient test report in the hospital, which showed that the patient tested positive for SARS coronavirus with high confidence. In order to remind students to pay attention to the point of view of protection (most of his classmates are clinical doctors) , he posted a paragraph of "south China seafood and fruit market confirmed 7 cases of SARS" in the Wechat Group of his college classmates. An hour later, he corrected in the group, "the latest news is that the coronavirus infection has been confirmed, the virus is typing, " and reminded everyone not to spread, let family members pay attention to prevention.

On the same day, Wuhan Health Commission Medical Administration Department issued "on doing a good job of unexplained pneumonia emergency notice. ". According to the notice, some medical institutions in Wuhan have been suffering from pneumonia of unknown cause. The notice requires the medical institutions to timely follow-up statistical treatment, and timely reporting as required. The notice stressed in particular that "without authorization any unit, individuals shall not release rescue information to the outside. ".

On December 31, the Wuhan Health Commission released the news of "pneumonia of unknown cause" , and relevant personnel from the National Health Commission also arrived in Wuhan to investigate.

On January 1,2020, the Wuhan Public Security Bureau tweeted that, "recently, some medical institutions in Wuhan have been found to have received many cases of pneumonia, and the Wuhan Health and Health Commission has issued an information circular on this issue. However, some netizens in the case of non-verified, in the network, the retransmission of false information, resulting in adverse social impact. The investigation confirmed that the local Public Security Bureau had summoned eight offenders and dealt with them in accordance with the law."

On January 3, Li Wenliang received a warning letter from the local police station for "making untrue statements on the Internet. ". He later said he had signed the document because he thought it was enough not to be detained.

Since then, Li's work has not been affected, still working in the hospital. On January 8, he treated an 82-year-old woman in hospital with acute angle-closure Glaucoma. Because the patient didn't have a fever, he didn't take any precautions. The next day, the patient had a fever and a CT scan showed a "double lung ground-glass lesion, " but the absence of a nucleic acid kit was not confirmed.

At noon on January 10, Li Wenliang began to cough without attracting attention.

On January 11, Li Wenliang developed a high fever, which peaked at 38.6 degrees. On the same day, he had a CT scan, which also showed "multiple lung infections, ground-glass Lesions. ". Because of the doctor's professional sensitivity, he imposed a self-imposed quarantine on the same day, staying outside the hotel.

On the same day, the Wuhan Municipal Commission of Health and viral pneumonia issued a report on the cause of the outbreak, saying that no medical staff had been found infected and no clear evidence of human to human transmission had been found.

On the afternoon of January 12, Li Wenliang was transferred to the hospital ward. His parents also developed fever, vomiting and ground-glass lung lesions that day and were hospitalized three days later.

On Jan. 24, Li was transferred to intensive-care unit, treated with antibiotics, hormones, antiviral drugs and high flow oxygen, and had his first nucleic acid test the same day, the results were unclear. Since then, he has had a second nucleic acid test, which came back negative, but the hospital has been treating him in accordance with clinical guidelines from the COVID-19, as a precaution.

On January 31, he had his third nucleic acid test, and the next day it was positive. He was diagnosed with COVID-19 pneumonia. "The dust has settled and we have a diagnosis, " he said on his social media platform that day. At the time, he was unable to speak through an oxygen tube and was able to communicate only through his mobile phone.

On January 28, a Supreme People's Court article said that "the Wuhan Public Security Bureau has punished eight people for publishing the 'seven confirmed SARS cases in the south China fruit and seafood market' " , saying that although the new type of pneumonia was not SARS, but what the publisher publishes is not a complete fabrication. If the public had listened to this "rumor" and, based on the panic over SARS, had taken measures such as wearing masks, strict disinfection, and avoiding going back to the wildlife market, this would have helped us better prevent and control the new type of pneumonia today, could be a blessing.

Zeng Guang, chief scientist of the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention and a member of the National Health Commission's senior Expert Group, said in an interview that, "These eight people are honorable, they are concerned about the country and the people, and they have opinions. As public health experts, we want to talk to them and learn from them. "

"after reading the Supreme Court article, I feel much more relaxed and less worried about the hospital's treatment, " Li said in an interview. "I think a healthy society should not have only one voice. ".

PROPHECY: You may not be able to reach me from today

Li Wenliang is an ordinary person who loves life.

From his micro blog, it can be seen that he likes Xiao Zhan, Bi Dao and Hu pu. He often reposts various kinds of lucky draw micro blogs, including giving away mobile phones, giving cars and centimeters, giving free travel, his pet son and wife, buying folic acid for his wife who is pregnant with their second child on micro blog, see others take photos of the Great Wall in autumn, said there is time to take Xiao Li (lover) to experience.

He likes good food, a bowl of $9 noodles, in his pen is: Noodles Flexible, red oil clear, beef firm, pickle acid cool... he will order two shops of chicken steak, and made a comparison..

Sometimes artsy, too, sharing "rolling stone's sudden release of an immortal hit will be better tomorrow in HD... "

More often than not, he focuses on electronics, and in his early years he used to score points on his phone, paying to see what Luo Yonghao had to say about the Iphone 11.

When Luo Yonghao launched his new phone, he also wanted to post: Last night I stayed in front of my computer and listened to two hours of cross talk. I went to Jd.com at 9:59 on the dot to make a purchase, but my wife stopped me in time. We had a Cold War for a whole night! The morning kiss was canceled, and a man can't get away without a little nest egg ！! By the way, when will 32G be available?

Yeah, he does that to himself sometimes.

There's also a lot about doctors on his Weibo. On December 28 last year, for example, two days before his classmates issued an alert, he turned to an article in support of Dr. Yang Wen of the Beijing Civil Aviation Hospital, titled "Hell Is Empty, the world of demons. ".

Sometimes it's a little work story, like, Oh, my God, it's 7:30, I'm bandaging my last female patient. PATIENT: You haven't eaten yet, have you? Me: Patient Service is the most important thing. What is eating? PATIENT: Well..

Weibo presents an ordinary Li Wenliang, living a very daily life.

At 1:41 a.m. on Feb. 7, Mr. Do, a doctor at the Wuhan Union Hospital and a colleague of Mr. Li's, shared a picture that read: There are no heroes who fall from the sky, only mortals who rise up.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Eight years ago on December 21,2012, the legendary "end of the world" . On that day, Li Wenliang tweeted:

Friends, you may not be able to reach me from today, because I'm off to save the planet. If The Sun Also Rises, that means I have succeeded, do not thank me, it is all right!
